From: Pawan Gupta <pawan.kumar.gupta@linux.intel.com>
Date: Wed, 30 Oct 2019 21:28:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] kvm: x86: mmu: Apply global mitigations knob to ITLB_MULTIHIT
Patch-mainline: Not yet, still under embargo
References: bnc#1117665

Problem: The global mitigation knob mitigations=off does not turn off
X86_BUG_ITLB_MULTIHIT mitigation.

Fix: Turn off the mitigation when ITLB_MULTIHIT mitigation mode is
"auto" and mitigations are turned off globally via cmdline
mitigations=off.

Signed-off-by: Pawan Gupta <pawan.kumar.gupta@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Michal Hocko <mhocko@suse.com>

---
Rebased on taa-master bundle. I do not have access to Thomas's repo.
This needs to go on top of Tyler's fix.

 Documentation/kernel-parameters.txt |    6 ++++++
 arch/x86/kvm/mmu.c                  |   10 ++++++++--
 2 files changed, 14 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/Documentation/kernel-parameters.txt
+++ b/Documentation/kernel-parameters.txt
@@ -1675,6 +1675,12 @@ bytes respectively. Such letter suffixes
 					       spec_store_bypass_disable=off [X86,PPC]
 					       l1tf=off [X86]
 					       mds=off [X86]
+					       kvm.nx_huge_pages=off [X86]
+
+				Exceptions:
+					       This does not have any effect on
+					       kvm.nx_huge_pages when
+					       kvm.nx_huge_pages=force.
 
 			auto (default)
 				Mitigate all CPU vulnerabilities, but leave SMT
--- a/arch/x86/kvm/mmu.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/mmu.c
@@ -3794,6 +3794,12 @@ static void mmu_destroy_caches(void)
 		kmem_cache_destroy(mmu_page_header_cache);
 }
 
+static bool get_nx_auto_mode(void)
+{
+	/* Return true when CPU has the bug, and mitigations are ON */
+	return has_bug_itlb_multihit() && !cpu_mitigations_off();
+}
+
 static void __set_nx_huge_pages(bool val)
 {
 	nx_huge_pages = itlb_multihit_kvm_mitigation = val;
@@ -3810,7 +3816,7 @@ static int set_nx_huge_pages(const char
 	else if (sysfs_streq(val, "force"))
 		new_val = 1;
 	else if (sysfs_streq(val, "auto"))
-		new_val = has_bug_itlb_multihit();
+		new_val = get_nx_auto_mode();
 	else if (strtobool(val, &new_val) < 0)
 		return -EINVAL;
 
@@ -3838,7 +3844,7 @@ static int set_nx_huge_pages(const char
 int kvm_mmu_module_init(void)
 {
 	if (nx_huge_pages == -1)
-		__set_nx_huge_pages(has_bug_itlb_multihit());
+		__set_nx_huge_pages(get_nx_auto_mode());
 
 	pte_chain_cache = kmem_cache_create("kvm_pte_chain",
 					    sizeof(struct kvm_pte_chain),
